   149	belongs (it is a §2 precondition rejection, not a §3.4 atomicity
   150	test).
   151	
   152	#### 3.1.b Group `Promotion preconditions` — citing chapter 06 §2
   153	
   154	Asserts the §2 promotion-trigger requirements on the wire-observable
   155	preconditions: status (a) and commit_sha-set (b). The §2 (c) branch-
   156	reachability condition is **off-wire** in v0 and is explicitly NOT
   157	asserted (per §2.1 above); a future binding chapter MAY add it.
   158	
   159	Each test asserts the **end-state**, not just the wire response, per
   160	the chunk-11c "end-state, not endpoint" pattern (
   161	[`conformance/README.md`](../../conformance/README.md)): the response
   162	is 4xx in `eden://error/invalid-precondition`, AND the trial's
   163	`trial_commit_sha` is unset, AND no `trial.integrated` event was
   164	appended for T. The composite end-state pins the §3.4 rollback-half
   165	"a failed write produces neither field nor event" without needing a
