 succeeded in 0ms:
   280	  `drive_to_error_trial(client, *, proposal_id=None) -> str` and
   281	  `drive_to_eval_error_trial(client, *, proposal_id=None) -> str`.
   282	  Both follow the chunk-11c hardening pattern: call
   283	  `raise_for_status()` on every wire call AND assert the end-state
   284	  trial status before returning. The `error`-trial helper drives
   285	  through `submit_implement(status="error")` + `accept`; the
   286	  `eval_error`-trial helper drives through `drive_to_starting_trial`
   287	  + `declare_trial_eval_error`. (Both helpers exist in
   288	  `_seed`'s prior surface; only the composite drive-to-end-state
   289	  helpers are new.)
   290	
   291	### 5.3 Repo metadata
   292	
   293	- `AGENTS.md` — current-phase header gains a chunk-11d-complete entry.
   294	- `docs/roadmap.md` — Phase 11 chunk 11d marked complete; Phase 11
   295	  exit criterion ("reference impl passes the full v1 suite; suite is
   296	  documented as the conformance contract for `eden-protocol/v0`")
   297	  marked met. Phase 11 itself transitions from chunk-pending to
   298	  fully complete.
   299	
   300	## 6. Reference-impl behavior (verification)
   301	
   302	The reference impl already supports all the wire-observable chapter-06
   303	projections via the `eden_storage._base.SqliteStore` /
   304	`PostgresStore` / `InMemoryStore` `integrate_trial` composite-commit:
   305	
   306	- `_accept_integrate` writes `trial_commit_sha` and `trial.integrated`
   307	  in one DB transaction (composite-commit invariant — chapter 05 §2.2).
   308	- The pre-commit precondition check rejects non-`success` trials with
   309	  `IllegalTransition` (mapped to 409 `invalid-precondition` at the
   310	  wire layer in `eden_wire.errors`).
   311	- A trial without `commit_sha` set is rejected the same way at integrate
   312	  time (the precondition check looks for `trial.commit_sha`).
   313	- Same-value retry is no-op (existing v1 test passes).
   314	- Different-value rejection raises `InvalidPrecondition` without
   315	  mutating state (existing v1 test passes; the new
   316	  `divergent-resubmit-leaves-no-second-event` test will still pass).
   317	
   318	The new tests are **not expected to fail** against the reference impl;
   319	they extend coverage rather than discovering new behavior. If any
   320	new test reveals a gap, it will surface at run time and the resolution
   321	is one of: amend the spec, fix the impl, fix the suite (per chapter 9
   322	§7 — the reference impl does not have authority to reinterpret the
   323	spec).
   324	
   325	## 7. Test-design notes
   326	
   327	### 7.1 Cross-artifact-consistency tests are stronger than per-artifact tests
   328	
   329	The chunk's central new content is the **cross-artifact consistency**
   330	assertion: it's not enough to verify "field is set" and "event was
   331	emitted" independently; the new tests assert that they reference the
   332	**same** SHA. A bug where the composite-commit writes the field but
   333	emits the event with a stale SHA (or vice versa) would not be caught
   334	by the existing v1 tests; it would be caught by the new tests.
   335	
   336	This is also the right shape because it's **wire-observable** — a
   337	client that reads the field and the event sees the same value.
   338	
   339	### 7.2 Helper hardening discipline (per chunk-11c codification)
   340	
   341	`drive_to_error_trial` and `drive_to_eval_error_trial` MUST verify
   342	their own postconditions before returning. Specifically:
   343	
   344	- `drive_to_error_trial` asserts `read_trial(...).get("status") ==
   345	  "error"` after `accept` of the implement task.
   346	- `drive_to_eval_error_trial` asserts `read_trial(...).get("status")
   347	  == "eval_error"` after `declare_trial_eval_error`.
   348	
   349	This matches the codified rule in
   350	[`conformance/README.md`](../../conformance/README.md) "Hardening
   351	setup helpers".
   352	
   353	### 7.3 Citation-check discipline
   354	
   355	Each test's docstring first line MUST cite a real chapter-06 MUST
   356	section. Each new scenario file MUST declare
   357	`CONFORMANCE_GROUP = '<group name>'`, where the group name matches
   358	one of the two new chapter-9 §5 entries. Each test's citation MUST
   359	fall inside its group's chapter-9 §5 entry's spec range.
   360	
   361	The check is automated by
   362	[`conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py`](../../conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py)
   363	and runs in CI after pytest. Adding a group to chapter 9 §5 without
   364	a citing test fails the check ("no valid citing test declares
   365	CONFORMANCE_GROUP = ... AND cites one of: ..."). Per-test
   366	group-relevance is also enforced.
   367	
   368	## 8. Verification plan
   369	
   370	Before opening the PR:
   371	
   372	1. `npx --yes markdownlint-cli2@0.14.0 "**/*.md" "#node_modules" "#.venv" "#docs/archive/**" "#docs/plans/review/**"`
   373	   passes — covers the chapter-9 amendment + the new plan + roadmap.
   374	2. `python3 scripts/spec-xref-check.py` passes — chapter-9 §4 amendment
   375	   may add cross-references (chapter 06 §3.4 / §2 / §5.3).
   376	3. `pipx run 'check-jsonschema==0.29.4' --check-metaschema spec/v0/schemas/*.schema.json`
   377	   passes — no schema changes expected, but defensive run.
   378	4. `uv run ruff check .` passes — new scenario files + harness extension.
   379	5. `uv run pyright` passes — typed harness extension; new scenarios
   380	   are type-checked.
   381	6. `uv run pytest -q` passes (full reference test suite, including
   382	   the chunk-11c v1+roles scenarios). Total scenario count rises
   383	   from 106 to ~111.
   384	7. `uv run python conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py`
   385	   passes — every new test cites a real MUST; every new group has a
   386	   valid citing test; per-test relevance check passes.
   387	8. CI on the PR is fully green (12 existing jobs).
   388	
   389	## 9. Risks
   390	
   391	### 9.1 Chapter-9 amendment scope creep
   392	
   393	The §4 amendment is a single paragraph that **scopes** v1+roles+integrator
   394	to wire-observable MUSTs. Codex review of the plan may push to also
   395	land the "future binding chapter for git-access conformance" prose.
   396	Decision: leave a forward-pointer in the amendment ("a future spec
   397	lineage MAY ...") but do **not** define that future contract in this
   398	chunk. Scope discipline > prose completeness.
   399	
   400	### 9.2 Citation-check group bleed
   401	
   402	The new `Promotion preconditions` group cites §2; the existing
   403	`Integrate idempotency` group cites chapter 7 §5, which itself
   404	**references** chapter 06 §3.4. The citation-check matches
   405	chapter+section pairs (it does NOT follow cross-references), so the
   406	two groups don't bleed at the check level. This is correct: the v1
   407	test cites the **HTTP-layer** rule; the v1+roles+integrator test
   408	cites the **integrator-layer** rule. Both citations are
   409	independently true MUSTs.
   410	
   411	### 9.3 Test redundancy
   412	
   413	The new `divergent-resubmit-leaves-no-second-event` test partially
   414	overlaps with the v1 `test_different_sha_returns_409` — both submit
   415	the same wire shape. Decision: keep both. Each cites a different
   416	chapter and asserts a different invariant (HTTP idempotency vs
   417	chapter-06 §5.3 no-overwrite). The test-redundancy cost is small
   418	(one wire round-trip) and the assertion strengthening is real
   419	(the new test additionally asserts the event log's cardinality).
   420	
   421	### 9.4 Trial-status helper coverage
   422	
   423	`drive_to_error_trial` exercises a path the existing test_implementer_submission.py
   424	already covers in chunk-11c (status=error terminalizes trial as
   425	error). The new helper just consolidates the harness shape. No
   426	spec-level surprise expected.
   427	
   428	`drive_to_eval_error_trial` uses `declare_trial_eval_error` directly
   429	(orchestrator-level call, exposed on the wire as `POST
   430	/trials/{T}/declare-eval-error`). The reference impl's

